<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 05 at 8:01AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Reduced Visibilities this Morning...
An area of fog has develop within the Helena Valley this morning,
generally along and east of the Interstate 15 corridor from
Highway 12 to the North Hill. This area of fog was shallow in
nature, and is expected to persist through 9am to 10am. Motorist
should be prepared for reduced visibilities to around 1/2 mile
from the Helena Airport north to Lake Helena. Slow down and use
your low beam headlights when driving through fog.</description>
